HEADWORD: Mussitation
<hw>Mus`si*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mussitatio</ets> suppression of the voice, fr. <ets>mussitare</ets>
to be silent, to murmur.]</ety> <def>A speaking in a low tone;
mumbling.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
